---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';

import '../styles/index.css';
import '../styles/cards.css';
import '../styles/about.css';
---


<Layout title="About Astrosyo">
  <main class="about-page page-home">
    <section class="hero about-hero">
      <span class="hero-kicker">Meet Astrosyo</span>
      <h1 class="home-title">Welcome to Astrosyo</h1>
      <p class="home-description">
        We’re passionate about making astronomy accessible, engaging, and fun for everyone. Whether you’re a curious beginner or a seasoned skywatcher, our guides, reviews, and simulations help you explore the cosmos with confidence.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="about-grid about-grid--notices">
      <article class="about-card">
        <h2>Why trust us?</h2>
        <p>
          Astrosyo is an astronomy blog created by experts in software and astronomy.
          Our writers <strong>Atakan Saraçyakupoğlu</strong> and <strong>Zane Landers</strong>
          provide trustworthy product insights, overviews, and reviews to help you with your stargazing adventures.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article class="about-card">
        <h2>Our Content Types</h2>
        <p>
          <strong>Review Posts</strong> are based on hands-on experience and direct testing of telescopes and astronomy gear.
          <strong>Overview Posts</strong> are based on in-depth research, manufacturer data, astronomy community feedback,
          and independent testing data from trusted sources. Both types aim to give you clear, honest, and useful information.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article class="about-card">
        <h2>Our Rating System</h2>
        <p>
          For review posts, our ratings are based on first-hand use and expert judgment.
          For overview posts, our ratings reflect aggregated insights from reputable sources and verified user experiences.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article class="about-card">
        <h2>Where to buy?</h2>
        <p>
          Consider choosing HighPointScientific as your main vendor for shipping safety and refunds.
          Amazon is viable, but has occasionally shipped astronomy gear with missing pieces and more complex refund processes.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article class="about-card">
        <h2>Affiliate Notice</h2>
        <p>
          We have affiliate programs with Amazon, HighPointScientific, and Astroshop.
          If you click on a link and make a purchase, we receive a small commission.
          Our content remains unbiased — your satisfaction matters more than short-term affiliate income.
        </p>
      </article>
    </section>

    <section class="about-grid">
      <article class="about-card">
        <h2>Our Mission</h2>
        <p>
          We believe the night sky holds endless wonder. Our mission is to provide honest, in-depth telescope reviews, practical observing tips, and educational articles that inspire you to look up, learn, and discover the universe.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article class="about-card">
        <h2>What We Cover</h2>
        <ul class="about-list">
          <li><strong>Telescope Reviews</strong> — Unbiased breakdowns of optics, mounts, and accessories.</li>
          <li><strong>How-To Guides</strong> — Step-by-step tutorials for beginners and advanced observers alike.</li>
          <li><strong>Astrophotography Tips</strong> — Techniques to capture stunning celestial images.</li>
          <li><strong>Astronomy News</strong> — Updates on discoveries, events, and space missions.</li>
        </ul>
      </article>

      <article class="about-card">
        <h2>Meet the Team</h2>
        <p>
          Our crew blends hands-on observing experience, academic research, and a love of teaching. From mirror grinding to mount engineering, each author brings a unique perspective to help you find the right gear and skywatching techniques.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article class="about-card about-card--cta">
        <h2>Join Us</h2>
        <p>
          Subscribe for monthly sky guides, exclusive discounts, and behind-the-scenes content. Connect with us on social media and become part of the Astrosyo community!
        </p>
        <a href="/newsletter" class="cta cta--primary about-cta">Subscribe Now</a>
      </article>
    </section>
  </main>
</Layout>